<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Cercocarpus</i> <i>ledifolius</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Amelanchier</i> <i>alnifolia</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>patula</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>tridentata</i>, <i>Chamaebatiaria</i> <i>millefolium</i>, <i>Chrysothamnus</i> <i>viscidiflorus</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>umbellatum</i>, <i>Holodiscus</i> <i>discolor</i>, <i>Prunus</i> <i>virginiana</i>, <i>Purshia</i> <i>tridentata</i>, <i>Ribes</i> <i>cereum</i> and <i>Ribes</i> <i>velutinum</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Juniperus</i> <i>occidentalis</i>, <i>Juniperus</i> <i>osteosperma</i>, <i>Pinus</i> <i>albicaulis</i>, <i>Pinus</i> <i>balfouriana</i>, <i>Pinus</i> <i>contorta</i> ssp. <i>murrayana</i>, <i>Pinus</i> <i>flexilis</i>, <i>Pinus</i> <i>jeffreyi</i> or <i>Pinus</i> <i>monophylla</i>. The herbaceous layer is typically grassy and associated species include <i>Bromus</i> <i>tectorum</i>, <i>Elymus</i> <i>elymoides</i> and <i>Poa</i> <i>secunda</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text"> Emergent trees may be present. Shrubs < 5 m; canopy is intermittent to open. Herbaceous layer is sparse to intermittent and commonly grassy. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Cercocarpus ledifolius</i> > 50% relative cover in the tall shrub or short tree canopy (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b, Thomas et al. 2004).</li>
		
		<li><i>Cercocarpus ledifolius</i> is >30% relative cover in the shrub layer. <i>Juniperus occidentalis</i> and <i>Pinus ponderosa</i> may be emergent in the tree layer (Boul et al. 2021b).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Ridges, upper slopes. Soils are shallow, and substrates are usually rocky, dry, and well drained.  </div>
</div>

        
